snippet.title: Pigeon Hole Principle (TANTON Mathematics)
snippet.description: In 1834 Dirichlet outined a very simple but extraordinarily powerful principle. I briefly discuss it here, and  then quickly move on to use it to solve a curious little puzzle I put out on twitter: Is there a power of three that ends with 001?
